title: For Sale:  Finnish M39 Mosin Nagant
postcontent:
This is a 1943 SAKO M39 (Finnish)  Mosin Nagant







This Rifle is a Antique



It has a 1898 Izhevsk Receiver



100% shiny mirror bore



Matching Bolt



SAKO Wartime stock/In very good condition



This rifle comes with a original leather Finn sling



This rifle like all M39's are great shooters.







In 1939 the Finnish Army and Civil Guard adopted a standard rifle known as the M39.   It is similar to previous models, but with improved barrel bands and a double sling swivel configuration making it suitable for all types of troops.   It is easily recognized by its pistol grip stock although early stocks are "straight" like the M27, M28, and M28/30.M39s were produced by SAKO (Suojeluskuntain Ase ja Konepaja Oy) and VKT (Valtion Kirvaaritehdas) and Tikkakoski M91 barrels were also cut down to build M39s.Some SAKO rifles have the Civil Guard Sk.Y (Suojeluskuntain Yliesikunta) logo and there are also "B" barrels fromBelgium although the rifles were assembled inFinland. M39s are well known for their accuracy and were produced for match shooting and training in the late '60s and early '70s.



Would look great in your collection.

title: For Sale:  Colt 1911A1 7.62x25 caliber all Colt parts exc
postcontent: This is a really interesting gun. There are quite a few 7.62x25 jungle conversions that came out of Vietnam and are mostly very crudely done out of a lot of worn and junk parts. This gun appears to be mostly WWII original Colt parts. I tried to show in the pictures the careful welding and machining that was done on this one. Notice how nicely the slide face is machined and the extractor moved over for the smaller cartridge head and the ejection port is opened for the longer case. Also look at the magazine well and how it is relieved both front and rear by machining instead of just grinding it larger. The High Standard barrel is sleeved and reworked and the bore and chamber are nice and shiny with no pitting or corrosion. When you look at the assembled gun it looks like a standard Colt until you look closely.
